15 SECTION 2.
16 Title 2 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to agriculture, is amended by
17 adding a new chapter to read as follows:
18 "CHAPTER 24
19 2-24-1.
20 (a) Effective July 1, 2025, the Center for Rural Prosperity and Innovation shall be
21 transferred from the University System of Georgia to the department and shall be
22 physically located within a department facility.
23 (b)(1) The director of the Center for Rural Prosperity and Innovation shall be appointed
24 by the Commissioner, provided that such appointment shall be subject to approval by a
25 majority vote of the Georgia Rural Development Council. The director shall continue to
26 serve in such position until his or her resignation or until the appointment of a new
27 director by the Commissioner, provided that such appointment is approved by a majority
28 vote of such council.
29 (2) Subject to appropriations, the director shall be authorized to employ such personnel
30 as are necessary to carry out the provisions of this chapter.
31 2-24-2.
32 (a) The Center for Rural Prosperity and Innovation shall assume the business and
33 responsibilities of the Centers of Innovation Agribusiness administered by the Department
34 of Economic Development.
35 (b) The Center for Rural Prosperity and Innovation, the Department of Economic
36 Development, and the department shall collaborate as necessary to achieve the mission
37 provided by Code Section 2-24-4.
