38 2-24-3.
39 (a) The Center for Rural Prosperity and Innovation shall include a council, to be known
40 and designated as the Georgia Rural Development Council, that shall offer guidance to the
41 Center for Rural Prosperity and Innovation.
42 (b) The Georgia Rural Development Council shall be composed of 12 members who shall
43 be appointed as follows:
44 (1) Six members shall be appointed by the Governor which six members, by majority
45 vote, shall appoint one of such members to serve as the chairperson of the council. Each
46 of the six shall be selected to represent one of the following areas:
47 (A) Leadership management;
48 (B) Business development and entrepreneurship;
49 (C) Finance and taxes;
50 (D) Logistics of rural industries;
51 (E) Healthcare; and
52 (F) Education;
53 (2) Three members who live in different geographic areas of this state from each other
54 shall be appointed by the Speaker of the House of Representatives; and
55 (3) Three members who live in different geographic areas of this state from each other
56 shall be appointed by the President of the Senate.
57 (c)(1) Legislative members who are appointed to the council shall serve for two-year
58 terms. Nonlegislative members shall serve for four-year terms, provided that three of the
59 initial six members to be appointed by the Governor shall serve initial terms of two years,
60 and thereafter such appointments shall be for four-year terms.
61 (2) Members may serve consecutive terms without limit.
62 (d)(1) The council shall study the conditions, needs, issues, and problems affecting rural
63 economic development and shall examine related policy areas as it may deem necessary
