65 infrastructure, education, unemployment, and economic growth incentives.
66 (2) All departments and agencies of the state, except the department, shall provide upon
67 request of the council services, information, and other support for the council and its
68 work.
69 (e) The chairperson shall call all meetings of the council. The council shall meet at least
70 once per quarter and each such meeting shall be at a different location within this state,
71 particularly in rural areas of this state, for the purpose of interacting with local government
72 officials, educational leaders, healthcare providers, business leaders, civic groups, and all
73 other citizens who desire to offer input, so as to enable the council to exercise fully and
74 effectively its powers, perform its duties, and accomplish the objectives and purposes of
75 this chapter.
76 (f)(1) Legislative members of the council shall receive the allowances provided for in
77 Code Section 28-1-8.
78 (2) Members of the council who are state officials, other than legislative members, or
79 state employees shall receive no compensation for their services on the council, but they
80 may be reimbursed for expenses incurred by them in the performance of their duties as
81 members of the council in the same manner as they are reimbursed for expenses in their
82 capacities as state officials or employees.
83 (3) Citizen members of the council shall receive a daily expense allowance in an amount
84 the same as that specified in subsection (b) of Code Section 45-7-21, as well as the
85 mileage or transportation allowance authorized for state employees.
86 (4) The allowances and expenses authorized by this subsection shall not be received by
87 the chairperson for more than 15 days and any other member of the council for more than
88 ten days per year. Funds necessary to carry out the provisions of this Code section shall
89 come from appropriated funds; provided, however, that funds for the reimbursement of
